To resemble the atchange script, try this usage of inotifywait:<p><pre><code>  while true; do inotifywait -qq -e modify [filename]; [command]; done
</code></pre>
or as a shell function, defined in .bashrc to have the same form as the atchange perl script:<p><pre><code>  function atchange(){
    while true;
    do inotifywait -qq -e modify $1;
    $2;
    done</code></pre>
